cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both the software itself (using the metadata below) and the accompanying peer-reviewed paper (see 'preferred-citation')."
type: software
title: "SimilCode Backend"
abstract: >
  REST API for source-code similarity analysis and Big O complexity
  estimation, powered by four commercial large language models used as
  similarity analysts (Claude Opus 4.1, GPT-5, Gemini 2.5 Pro, DeepSeek-V3).
  Designed as a screening aid for academic-integrity workflows in
  resource-constrained higher-education institutions. Supported source
  languages in this release: C# and Java.
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-07-07"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/gleiston-guerrero/BackEnd-SimilCode"
url: "https://github.com/gleiston-guerrero/BackEnd-SimilCode"
keywords:
  - source-code similarity
  - academic integrity
  - plagiarism detection
  - large language models
  - LLM
  - programming education
  - Big O complexity
  - screening tool
  - Django
  - REST API
  - Claude
  - GPT-5
  - Gemini
  - DeepSeek

